          "conformsTo": "http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/",
          "value": "xywh=pixel:916.4366640440599,5234.303697875688,3785.5232100708104,1142.4075531077906"
        }
      },
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "Great is peace, for peace is to the world as leaven is to dough. Perek HaShalom 1:1\nBy three things does the world endure: justice, truth, and peace. R. Muna said: The three are one\nbecause if justice is done, truth has been effected and peace is brought about. Perek HaShalom 1:2\nGreat is peace, for even in a time of war one should begin (by attempting to arrange) peace.\nPerek HaShalom 1:14\nNN Lo yisa goi... Nation shall not... Isaiah 2:4",
          "language": "en"
        }
      ],
